This paper focuses on developing a machine learning model for content selection in task-oriented dialogue systems. This falls under the category of natural language processing and specifically dialogue systems, which is covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of machine learning algorithms and feature sets also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of rule-induction programs, which falls under the category of machine learning and specifically classification, making cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which is covered by cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of discourse structure, which is covered by cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
